articles.description: The New York Jets played another horrible defensive game Sunday in their 45-17 loss to the Buffalo Bills at MetLife Stadium, creating new marks for futility and roiling emotions in the locker room.
articles.headline: New York Jets' blowout loss to Buffalo Bills brings new marks for defensive futility

images.name: Austin Ekeler jams on fan's blow up guitar after TD
images.caption: Austin Ekeler strums a fan's inflatable guitar after scoring a go-ahead touchdown for the Chargers.

articles.description: — Kirk Cousins threw a pair of touchdown passes to Tyler Conklin, Dalvin Cook rushed for 94 yards and a score, and the Minnesota Vikings bounced back after a trying couple of weeks to defeat the Los Angeles Chargers 27-20 Sunday.
articles.headline: Cousins throws 2 TDs, Vikings bounce back to beat Chargers

images.name: Pete Carroll can't find his challenge flag, throws hand warmer instead
images.caption: Pete Carroll has a hard time finding the challenge flag in his pocket so he decides to throw his hand warmer instead.

articles.description: — Aaron Rodgers was uneven in his return from COVID-19 but did more than enough to support a standout Green Bay Packers defense in a 17-0 victory over the Seattle Seahawks on Sunday.
articles.headline: Packers blank Seahawks 17-0 as Rodgers, Wilson return
